  const users = getUsers(); // from DB
  const safeUsers = users.map(({ id, name }) => ({ id, name })); // omit email
  res.json(safeUsers);
});
```

---

#### 5. No Request Body Parsing / Input Validation (Injection Risk — OWASP A03)

`app.use(express.json())` is never registered. Any future `POST`/`PUT`/`PATCH` routes that rely on `req.body` will silently receive `undefined`, bypassing validation logic. This is a latent vulnerability that will cause bugs or injection risks as the app grows.

**Fix — add body parsing with a size limit:**
```js
