app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false, limit: '10kb' }));
```

---

#### 6. No CORS Policy

The app sets no CORS headers, which means: in permissive environments (some server configs) any origin can call the API. In strict environments, legitimate clients may be blocked without clear errors.

**Fix:**
```js
const cors = require('cors');

app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourdomain.com'],  // explicit allowlist
  methods: ['GET', 'POST'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Authorization', 'Content-Type'],
}));
```

---

#### 7. Verbose Error Handling / Information Leakage (OWASP A05)

Express's default error handler will expose full stack traces in development and potentially in production if `NODE_ENV` is not set. No custom error handler is defined.

**Fix — add a global error handler:**
```js
