User data is hardcoded inline in the route handler. When real database queries are introduced, injection risks (SQL/NoSQL injection) will need to be explicitly mitigated. Use parameterized queries (e.g., with `pg`, `mysql2`, or an ORM like Prisma) and never interpolate user input into query strings.

